 British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Susana Carter, (is this his first wife?), Wm *hirt?, Mary Smythe, An Hughs, Jos Maxy, Mark Smythe, ???? Lu*ard?\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Bought John Carter's plantation, the 800 acre Barford plantation\",\"d\":\"18 September 1655\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"£412 curr monie of England to be paid in London to John Carter of Lancaster county by 10 Jun 1657, or perhaps in tobacco, plantation of John Carter, formerly Capt Wm Brocas. Diana Skipwith a witness.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Bought 560 acres from George Marsh on credit\",\"d\":\"14 January 1656\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"8000 pounds tobacco, 4000 due 10 Oct 1658, the other 400 due one year later. Recorded 28 Jul 1657\"},{\"t\":\"MILITARY_SERVICE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"about 1660\",\"pl\":\"Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Divided the 400 acres he owned with Ebbya Bonnison\",\"d\":\"2 August 1660\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, United States\",\"desc\":\" Beginning at head of cove out of branch of Haddaways Creek, cove Corotomen Creek, Bonnison's land downward upon the Bay, above the marked trees Hugh Brent is contented to take.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Capt Thomas Carter, Court Justice\",\"d\":\"29 March 1664\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"MILITARY_SERVICE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1667\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Captain Lancaster Militia\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Marriage to Katharine Dale\",\"d\":\"4 May 1670\",\"pl\":\"Lancaster, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"Marriage\"},{\"t\":\"OCCUPATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1671\",\"pl\":\"Virginia, United States\",\"desc\":\"Deputy Clerk for Edward Dale Lancaster Clerk of Court\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Creditor in Lancaster County, Virginia\",\"