T\",\"ti\":\"Alt. Burial\",\"d\":\"15 October 1726\",\"pl\":\"New Garden, New Garden Township, Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"WILL - Chester Co, Pennsylvania - Book 1 pg 210\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"WILL of James Lindley of London Grove, smith - wife Elinor - sons Thomas, James, Robert & William minors - son Jonathan - daughters Rachel, Margery, Alice, Mary, Elizabeth & Hannah are all minors younger than 21 years - overseers are friends James Star & Benjamin Fred both of New Garden - written 8 Dec 1726 - probated 2 Jan 1726/7\"},{\"t\":\"OCCUPATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"New Garden, Chester, Pennsylvania, United States\",\"desc\":\"Blacksmith, Constable 1723\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"New Garden, Chester, Pennsylvania, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Died at age of 45\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"In 1726 James died, leaving Eleanor pregnant with another child, a daughter who was born after his death (Eleanor1727)\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"London Grove Township, Chester, Pennsylvania, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Chester, Delaware, Pennsylvania, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":25,\"src\":53},{\"pos\":816,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"9CJ7-RTP\",\"name\":\"James Lindley, Sr.\",\"life\":\"1641–1714\",\"bp\":\"Cheshire, England\",\"dp\":\"Ballymore Eustace, County Kildare, Ireland\",\"states\":[\"Pennsylvania\"],\"primary\":\"Pennsylvania\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Alt. Birth\",\"d\":\"1641\",\"pl\":\"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Quaker record - Ireland births\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"James Linley son of John Linley was born in Cheshire 1641. He came into Ireland in the year 1670. Hee tooke to wife Alice the daughter of Thomas Wilsmoth, born in Yorkshire, and had issue by her - viz    **1678 Martha a daughter born at Cronasallagh in the county of Wicklow ye 14th of the 2nd month.    **1681 James a son born at Ballynaclash in the county aforsaid ye 16th of 4th month.    **1684 Thomas a son born at the place aforesaid the 11th of the 1st momth    **1687 Mary a daughter borne at the place aforesaid the 6th of the 8th month    **Alice the wife of the said James Lindley deceased\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Quaker Records - Ireland Burials\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"  **1691 Mary a daughter of James Linley dyed the 1st day of the 11th month and was buried at Friends Burying Place at Ballymorren   **1691 Alice the wife of said James Lindley dyed the 16th day of the same month and was buried at the place aforesaid  **1711 James Lindley, age 73 of Temulin, co Wicklow, husband of Alice & Elizabeth died 16th of 5th month and buried at Ballymorane\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Chester, Pennsylvania, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":6,\"src\":11},{\"pos\":409,\"gen\":11,\"id\":\"LR1W-8TL\",\"name\":\"Eleanor Elizabeth Parke\",\"life\":\"1684–1748\",\"bp\":\"Ballyredmond, Moyacomb, County Carlow, Ireland\",\"dp\":\"Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Pennsylvania\",\"North Carolina\"],\"primary\":\"Pennsylvania\",\"score\":5,\"interesting\":true,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Immigration\",\"d\":\"1713\",\"pl\":\"Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"James Lindley\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1755\",\"pl\":\"Orange, North Carolina, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"51 when last child was born\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Despite her age, Eleanor and Henry had three more children (James1731, Sarah Jane1733, and Isaac1735). They are mentioned numerous times in New Garden Quaker records, along with the Lindley children, so we can confirm her age and number of births. I have seen several instances of Quaker women who give birth to many children and remained fertile well into their forties, but Eleanor was 51 when her last child was born.\"},{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":8,\"src\":51},{\"pos\":818,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"PS9B-Q7R\",\"name\":\"Robert Parke\",\"life\":\"1650–1738\",\"bp\":\"County Carlow, Ireland\",\"dp\":\"Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Pennsylvania\",\"Oregon\"],\"primary\":\"Pennsylvania\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Arrival\",\"d\":\"1724\",\"pl\":\"Rivera, Multnomah, Oregon, United States\",\"desc\":\"\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Other\",\"d\":\"20 May 1726\",\"pl\":\"Ireland\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":0,\"src\":3},{\"pos\":1636,\"gen\":13,\"id\":\"GKQH-ZTF\",\"name\":\"Thomas Parke\",\"life\":\"1636–1736\",\"bp\":\"Ireland\",\"dp\":\"Saint Pauls Parish, Kent, Maryland, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Maryland\"],\"primary\":\"Maryland\",\"score\":0,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"CAUTION! NO TRUSTWORTHY SOURCES! 2025-07-17\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":0,\"src\":0},{\"pos\":1637,\"gen\":13,\"id\":\"KJL5-Z4Q\",\"name\":\"Rebecca Ward\",\"life\":\"1642–1695\",\"bp\":\"County Carlow, Ireland\",\"dp\":\"St Pauls Parish, Kent, Maryland, United States\",\"states\":[\"Maryland\"],\"primary\":\"Maryland\",\"score\":0,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":0,\"src\":1},{\"pos\":819,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"LKGJ-J4Z\",\"name\":\"Margery Medowe\",\"life\":\"1655–1738\",\"bp\":\"Ballykine, County Wicklow, Ireland\",\"dp\":\"East Caln Township, Chester, Pennsylvania, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Pennsylvania\"],\"primary\":\"Pennsylvania\",\"score\":0,\"interest