\",\"ti\":\"Birthplace\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Born in Ireland or Scotland? People on Ancestry lean toward Scotland (many have a specific location in Scotland - Aberdeen) although a minority do say Ireland. However, the surname Ogilvie or Ogilvy is clearly a Scot surname with origins in the Barony of Ogilvy in Angus, Scotland. It is even the name of a Scot clan. I have never been able to find proof of either and no one has provided that here.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Birthplace\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Doesn't anyone notice that his father was a nobleman in SCOTLAND. Born & died there. How could anyone imagine he was born in Ireland? A Scottish nobleman would NEVER cross the Irish Sea to give birth to a baby!\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":4,\"src\":9},{\"pos\":1177,\"gen\":11,\"id\":\"9N9H-69L\",\"name\":\"Bettie Elizabeth Riske\",\"life\":\"1695–1731\",\"bp\":\"Middlesex, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"North Carolina, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Virginia\",\"North Carolina\"],\"primary\":\"Virginia\",\"score\":0,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":0,\"src\":9},{\"pos\":589,\"gen\":10,\"id\":\"L4SY-DC5\",\"name\":\"Mary Harris\",\"life\":\"1735–1807\",\"bp\":\"Hanover, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"College Grove, Williamson, Tennessee, United States\",\"states\":[\"Virginia\",\"Tennessee\"],\"primary\":\"Virginia\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Ref #\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"L4SY-DC5\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":2,\"src\":4},{\"pos\":1178,\"gen\":11,\"id\":\"K6QV-P1G\",\"name\":\"Robert Harris III\",\"life\":\"1709–1786\",\"bp\":\"St. Peter's Parish, New Kent, Virginia, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Granville, North Carolina, United States\",\"states\":[\"Virginia\",\"North Carolina\"],\"primary\":\"Virginia\",\"score\":1,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1710\",\"pl\":\"Bertie,