n Conanicut Island and Newport by 1675. In 1678, Conanicut Island was incorporated as the town of Jamestown,[6] when there were about 150 residents. It was named for James, Duke of York, who became King James II in 1685.[7]\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":27,\"src\":32},{\"pos\":3163,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"LV76-QQ7\",\"name\":\"Sarah Clarke\",\"life\":\"1651–1706\",\"bp\":\"Newport, Newport, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Newport, Newport, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Relationships\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Daughter of Gov. Jeremiah Clark and brother to Gov. Walter Clark\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":3,\"src\":10},{\"pos\":791,\"gen\":10,\"id\":\"MCJ1-T2M\",\"name\":\"Mary Greene\",\"life\":\"1706–1757\",\"bp\":\"Warwick, Kent, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Warwick, Kent, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":0,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":0,\"src\":7},{\"pos\":1582,\"gen\":11,\"id\":\"LCBW-L22\",\"name\":\"Richard Greene\",\"life\":\"1660–1711\",\"bp\":\"Warwick, Kent, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Warwick, Kent, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":8,\"src\":36},{\"pos\":3164,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"LZGX-VLX\",\"name\":\"Maj John Greene\",\"life\":\"1620–1708\",\"bp\":\"Salisbury, Wiltshire, England\",\"dp\":\"Warwick, Providence, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":28,\"interesting\":true,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"IMMIGRATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"3 June 1635\",\"pl\":\"Providence, Providence, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"He may have immigrated on the sh