},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Probate\",\"d\":\"20 December 1708\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Will proved \"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Fact\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"His children were all born at Occupasuetaxet\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":33,\"src\":83},{\"pos\":3165,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"LZ68-2X1\",\"name\":\"Ann Almy\",\"life\":\"1627–1709\",\"bp\":\"South Kilworth, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom\",\"dp\":\"Warwick, Kent, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":3,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Emigration\",\"d\":\"1635\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"in the \\\"Abigail\\\" from London\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":17,\"src\":66},{\"pos\":1583,\"gen\":11,\"id\":\"KN77-JMP\",\"name\":\"Elinor Sayles\",\"life\":\"1671–1714\",\"bp\":\"Providence, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Warwick, Providence, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"memorial ID 17902988\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":6,\"src\":28},{\"pos\":3166,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"L5XJ-6JS\",\"name\":\"John Sayles\",\"life\":\"1633–1681\",\"bp\":\"England\",\"dp\":\"Newport, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":3,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"OCCUPATION\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"1659\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Town treasurer from 1659-1660\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Proof his wife was a daughter of Roger Williams is found in the following deed: Early Town Records of Providence Vol. XIV Deed Book 1, p.253  24 Jun 1670.  I John Sayles...have bargained & Sold unto Stephen Arnold of Pautuxett ..a full Thirteenth part of a little Island undivided called ye Vineyard. ...may Containe about a quarter of an acre for which I have received five shillings in Tobacco, which was the full Sum & price I sold it for.  I cannot make a firme deed of the forest land, at presant because I have None myself yet of My ffatherin-law Mr. Roger williams.  The forest land he gave me\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"No proof of birth date or location - There is no document showing John's place or date of birth - he was age 48 at his death or born about 1633.  He cannot be the man who first appears in the Providence records in 1645 as he would have been a child, but whether or not that earlier John was his father is not documented, but the relationship is possible.  No other parent has been found for John\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_EVENT\",\"ti\":\"Note\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"NOT a son of the Dutch John Sayles and wife Phillip Soales. That John and wife Phillip had ONLY TWO DAUGHTERS.  PLEASE READ all notes and discussions.\"},{\"t\":\"OTHER_FACT\",\"ti\":\"TEN CHILDREN\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"\",\"desc\":\"Ten Children:  Mary m. John Holmes, John II, Deborah m. Caleb Carr, Isabel m. John Tillinghast and 2nd to Robert Hicks, Phebe m. Job Greene, Anne, Richard, Thomas, Eleanor m. Richard Greene and Catherine m. William Olney\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":12,\"src\":17},{\"pos\":3167,\"gen\":12,\"id\":\"LRSV-ZGT\",\"name\":\"Mary Williams\",\"life\":\"1633–1681\",\"bp\":\"Plymouth Colony, British Colonial America\",\"dp\":\"Providence, Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"states\":[\"Rhode Island\"],\"primary\":\"Rhode Island\",\"score\":2,\"interesting\":false,\"ev\":[{\"t\":\"RESIDENCE\",\"ti\":\"\",\"d\":\"\",\"pl\":\"Rhode Island, British Colonial America\",\"desc\":\"\"}],\"sketch\":\"\",\"mem\":8,\"src\":24},{\"pos\":99,\"gen\":7,\"id\":\"K8Z6-W16\",\"name\":\"Rachel Wheat\",\"life\":\"1780–Deceased\",\"bp\":\"Red River, Louisiana, United States\",\"dp\":\"\",\"states\":[\"Louisiana\"],\"primary\":\"Louisiana\",\"score\":0,\"interesting